headline: Bull market still deserves the benefit of the doubt, Truist’s Lerner says
summary: Investing.com -- Truist’s Keith Lerner says the U.S. bull market remains firmly intact as the cycle enters what he calls the “seventh inning stretch,” arguing that neither the economic expansion nor the equity rally is near the end.

headline: How Recent Developments Are Shaping The Leidos Holdings Investment Story
summary: Leidos Holdings has seen its narrative evolve even as the stock’s fair value estimate held steady at $218.08 per share, with only a slight uptick in the discount rate to 7.56% reflecting a marginally higher risk environment. This measured shift is rooted in a mix of bullish enthusiasm over a robust contract pipeline and diversified growth opportunities, tempered by cautious views around government funding risks and valuation headwinds. Read on to see how you can stay on top of these narrative...

headline: Why The Narrative Around DoorDash Is Shifting Amid Fresh Analyst Updates And New Risks
summary: DoorDash's narrative on Wall Street has shifted subtly but meaningfully, with the Consensus Analyst Price Target nudging higher from $275.20 to $276.17 as analysts factor in stronger core marketplace momentum and improving revenue visibility. Slight upticks in the discount rate and revenue growth forecasts signal that while the risk profile is being reassessed, confidence in the company’s ability to translate expanding gross order value into durable top line strength remains intact.
